sible introduction to biblical epic poetry. Patrick McBrine's erudite analysis of the writings of Juvencus, Cyprianus, Arator, Bede, Alcuin, and more reveals the development of a hybridized genre of writing that informed and delighted its Christian audiences to such an extent it was copied and promoted for the better part of a millennium. The volume contains many first-time readings and discussions of poems and passages which have long lain dormant and offers new evidence for the reception of the Bible in late Antiquity and the Middle Ages.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aChristian poetry, LatinxHistory and criticism. 0aChristianity and literaturezEnglandxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aEpic poetry, LatinxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP eBook-Package Pilot 2017z978311066594908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2019z978311065878108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2016-2017z978311060680508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press ebook package 2017z978311063896740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781487514280423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487514280.jpg  a978-3-11-060680-5  University of Toronto Press Pilot 2016-2017  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-063896-7  University of Toronto Press ebook package 2017b2017